### API Request Sandbox
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/v1
@contentType = application/json

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 1. Register Account
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "vijay@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123!",
  "firstName": "Vijay",
  "lastName": "Singh",
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890"
}

### 2. Login Account
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "vijay@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123!"
}

### Save Token from Login response
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}

### 3. Active Sessions (Requires Bearer Token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/sessions
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 4. Rotate Session (Refresh Tokens)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

# Note: The refresh endpoint reads the HTTP-Only cookie automatically.
# You can also pass it in the JSON body if test environments require it.
{
  "refreshToken": ""
}

### 5. Forgot Password Reset Request
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "vijay@example.com"
}

### 6. Log Out Session
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
